  "title": "Planning Manager (Aerospace)",
  "description": "<p><strong>Job Description</strong></p><ul><li>Responsible managing Value Streams along with operations and engineering to ensure capacity matches requirements availability and order placement, identification and management of outside service providers, logistics coordination, and on-time starts.</li><li>In charge of planning and directing all resources and activities associated with production scheduling and planning, to achieve required business results.</li><li>In charge of leading a team of planners to ensure on-time release of work orders, monitor, measure, and address gaps with applicable parties to achieve divisional goals and 100% on-time delivery to the end customer.</li><li>Responsible in forecasting  intra-company needs in coordination with production planning, utilizing the appropriate material requirements planning systems/programs and lean practices.</li><li>Taking charge of own end-to-end SIOP process to manage change customer signals with operational Master Production Schedule to create One Plan for the site</li><li>Taking charge in managing  the monitoring, tracking and expediting for OV deliveries to support build plan working with related parties of procurement and Engineering.</li><li>Formulate build plan based on load capacity analysis.</li><li>In charge of managing critical inventory processes such as cycle counting, planning parameters,capacity analysis and demand planning processes</li><li>Monitor and report on supplier performance and implement corrective action when required to meet customer demand.</li><li>In charge of formulating and supporting cost reduction goals and initiatives.</li><li>Other related duties and projects as assigned.</li></ul><p><strong>Requirements</strong></p><ul><li>Min Degree in Business or Engineering Related</li><li>Min 5 year of experience in Operations Planning / SCM experience manufacturing industry.</li><li>Experience in production flow, inventory flow, and documentation procedures</li></ul><p>To submit your application, please apply online <a href=\"mailto:apply@rn-care.com\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\"><strong>apply@rn-care.com</strong></a><strong> </strong>or call<strong> </strong><a href=\"tel:+(65)%C2%A06513 5697\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\"><strong>+(65) 6513 5697</strong></a> for private and confidential discussion.</p><p>Your interest will be treated with the strictest of confidence. We regret that only shortlisted candidates will be notified or contacted.</p><p><strong>RN Care Pte. Ltd</strong><br /><strong>EA License No: 17C8900</strong></p>",
